  "name": "Lightning Stroke",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\">[Uncommon][Evocation][Electricity][Dynamic Heightening]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Traditions </strong>arcane, primal</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Access </strong>pegasus or griffon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Cast </strong>[two-actions] verbal, somatic</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Range </strong>60 feet</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Lashing out at a fog or cloud effect, you cause lightning to lash out with a moment of ominous rumbling. The target, who must be in range and inside the fog/cloud, must make a basic Reflex save against 3d6 electricity damage. If they are holding a metal item or wearing metal armor, their save takes a -1 penalty.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) You may target an additional creature within range that is inside the same cloud/fog.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) The target(s) may be up to 15 feet outside the cloud and the range of the spell increases to 90 feet.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Heightened </strong>(+1) Increase the damage by 1d6 and deal/increase 1 persistent electricity damage.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>"
